# EduCAT Backend — AI Exam Study System

This is the backend for EduCAT, an AI-powered exam study platform for Grade 12 CAT students.

It is built using Flask and deployed on PythonAnywhere. The system uses an AI agent (not a basic chatbot) to help students study, write exams, and improve based on their performance.

---

## Overview

The backend handles:

- AI tutoring via an agent-based system
- Exam simulation and answer submission
- Automatic marking of different question types
- Student progress tracking and weak topic detection
- Retrieval of theory content using RAG (FAISS)
- Persistent student memory using SQLite

The AI decides what to do based on the student’s input and history, instead of following fixed logic.

---

## How the AI Agent Works

The system uses a loop where the AI can decide to call tools before responding.

Example flow:
1. Student sends a message
2. AI checks memory (weak topics, history)
3. AI decides whether to:
   - search theory
   - generate a hint
   - update study plan
4. AI returns a final response

This allows dynamic and personalised behaviour for each student.

---

## API Endpoints

Base URL (production):
```

[https://abitonp.pythonanywhere.com](https://abitonp.pythonanywhere.com)

````

Main routes:

- `POST /agent-chat` → chat with AI agent
- `POST /start-exam` → start exam session
- `POST /question` → get a question
- `POST /answer` → save an answer
- `POST /submit` → submit and mark exam
- `POST /dashboard` → get student progress
- `POST /clear-history` → reset conversation

---

## Memory System (SQLite)

The backend stores student data locally in SQLite:

- students → identity
- sessions → exam results
- weak_questions → tracks mistakes
- conversation_history → chat logs
- study_plan → personalised plan

This memory is used by the AI on every request.

---

## Exam Engine

Supports:

- Multiple Choice (exact match)
- True/False
- Matching questions
- Open-ended questions (AI marking)

Each question contains its own memo (`q["memo"]`), ensuring correct marking.

---

## RAG (Theory Search)

- Uses FAISS for similarity search
- Retrieves relevant textbook content
- Injects context into AI responses

---

## Tech Stack

- Python (Flask)
- Groq LLM (llama-3.3-70b)
- SQLite
- FAISS

---

## Local Setup

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-repo.git
cd your-repo

pip install flask flask-cors groq python-dotenv faiss-cpu

echo "GROQ_API_KEY=your_key" > .env

python app.py
````

Runs on:

```
http://localhost:8000
```

---

## Deployment

The backend is deployed on PythonAnywhere:

* Flask app configured via WSGI
* Environment variable for API key
* SQLite database created automatically

